The Top Women in Business (WIB) Awards 2019 were held at the Movenpick Hotel on November 7. The awards sought to acknowledge the roles played by women in business in building the economy through creation of jobs and increasing the national income. Among those awarded were State Department of Correctional Services PS  Zeinab Hussein, Credit Bank’s senior manager Pamela Mutembei and Bonfire Adventures’ Sarah Kabu. Those in attendance included WIB president and CEO Mary Muthoni,  Kenya Trust CEO Dr Stanley Kamau and Makueni governor’s Nazi Kivutha. The chief guest was industrialist Manu Chandaria.